msgstr "3. The training rule on lewd speech"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.128, pts-vp-en1.214, pts-cs-bu-ss3.1.1, ms1V_1133 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anātha­piṇḍi­kassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī araññe viharati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was staying in the wilderness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.3"
msgid "Tassāyasmato vihāro abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko."
msgstr "in a beautiful dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā itthiyo ārāmaṃ āgamaṃsu vihā­ra­pekkhi­kāyo."
msgstr "Just then a number of women came to the monastery to see the dwellings."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.5"
msgid "Atha kho tā itthiyo yenāyasmā udāyī tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "They approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.7"
msgid "“icchāma mayaṃ, bhante, ayyassa vihāraṃ pekkhitun”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, we would like to see your dwelling.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.8"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tā itthiyo vihāraṃ pekkhāpetvā tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ vaccamaggaṃ passāvamaggaṃ ādissa vaṇṇampi bhaṇati avaṇṇampi bhaṇati yācatipi āyācatipi pucchatipi paṭipucchatipi ācikkhatipi anusāsatipi akkosatipi."
msgstr "Then, after showing them his own dwelling, he praised and disparaged their private parts; he requested and implored, asked and enquired, described, instructed, and abused."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.9"
msgid "Yā tā itthiyo chinnikā dhuttikā ahirikāyo tā āyasmatā udāyinā saddhiṃ uhasantipi ullapantipi ujjagghantipi uppaṇḍentipi."
msgstr "Those women among them who were wanton and shameless flirted with Udāyī; they called out to him, laughed with him, and made fun of him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.10"
msgid "Yā pana tā itthiyo hirimanā tā nikkhamitvā bhikkhū ujjhāpenti—"
msgstr "But, after leaving, those among them who had a sense of shame complained to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.11"
msgid "“idaṃ, bhante, nacchannaṃ nappatirūpaṃ."
msgstr "“Venerables, this isn’t suitable and appropriate."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.1.12"
msgid "Sāmikenapi mayaṃ evaṃ vuttā na iccheyyāma, kiṃ panāyyena udāyinā”ti."
msgstr "We wouldn’t want to hear this from our own husbands, let alone from Venerable Udāyī.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs-bu-ss3.1.2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.1"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.215
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.2"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.3"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī speak lewdly to women?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_1134 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.4"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They rebuked Udāyī in many ways and told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "And the Master had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you spoke lewdly to women?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.8"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.9"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“It’s not suitable, foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a recluse, it’s not allowable, it should not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.10"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāsissasi."
msgstr "How can you speak lewdly to women?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.11"
msgid "Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito no sarāgāya … pe …"
msgstr "Haven’t I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake of passion …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.12"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "for the stilling of the fevers of sense desire?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: yathā taṃ → yathātaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: methu­nu­pa­saṃhi­tāhi → methu­nū­pa­sañ­hi­tāhi (bj, s1-3)
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss3:1.2.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena mātugāmaṃ duṭṭhullāhi vācāhi obhāseyya yathā taṃ yuvā yuvatiṃ methu­nu­pa­saṃhi­tāhi, saṃghādiseso”ti."
